title: AbstractBlobStore
name: AbstractBlobStore

abiDocs.name: getFlags
abiDocs.details: Get all a blob's flags.

abiDocs.name: getExists
abiDocs.details: Check if a blob exists.
abiDocs.return: exists True if the blob exists.

abiDocs.name: transferEnable
abiDocs.details: Enable transfer of the blob to the current user.

abiDocs.name: getAllRevisionBlockNumbers
abiDocs.details: Get the block numbers for all of a blob's revisions.

inputs.name: contents
inputs.description: Contents of the blob to be stored.

abiDocs.name: create
abiDocs.details: Creates a new blob. It is guaranteed that different users will never receive the same blobId, even before consensus has been reached. This prevents blobId sniping. Consider createWithNonce() if not calling from another contract.

abiDocs.name: getRetractable
abiDocs.details: Determine if a blob is retractable.
abiDocs.return: retractable True if the blob is blob retractable.

abiDocs.name: getUpdatable
abiDocs.details: Determine if a blob is updatable.
abiDocs.return: updatable True if the blob is updatable.

abiDocs.name: getRevisionCount
abiDocs.details: Get the number of revisions a blob has.
abiDocs.return: revisionCount How many revisions the blob has.

abiDocs.name: getContractId
abiDocs.details: Get the id for this BlobStore contract.

abiDocs.name: transferDisable
abiDocs.details: Disable transfer of the blob to the current user.

inputs.name: flagsNonce
inputs.description: First 4 bytes: Packed blob settings. The parameter as a whole must never have been passed to this function from the same account, or it will throw.

inputs.name: contents
inputs.description: Contents of the blob to be stored.

abiDocs.name: createWithNonce
abiDocs.details: Creates a new blob using provided nonce. It is guaranteed that different users will never receive the same blobId, even before consensus has been reached. This prevents blobId sniping. This method is cheaper than create(), especially if multiple blobs from the same account end up in the same block. However, it is not suitable for calling from other contracts because it will throw if a unique nonce is not provided.

abiDocs.name: setEnforceRevisions
abiDocs.details: Set a blob to enforce revisions.

abiDocs.name: setNotRetractable
abiDocs.details: Set a blob to not be retractable.

inputs.name: contents
inputs.description: Contents that should replace the latest revision.

abiDocs.name: updateLatestRevision
abiDocs.details: Update a blob's latest revision.

abiDocs.name: retractLatestRevision
abiDocs.details: Retract a blob's latest revision. Revision 0 cannot be retracted.

abiDocs.name: createNewRevision
abiDocs.details: Create a new blob revision.

abiDocs.name: getTransferable
abiDocs.details: Determine if a blob is transferable.
abiDocs.return: transferable True if the blob is transferable.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.description: Address of the user to transfer to blob to.

abiDocs.name: transfer
abiDocs.details: Transfer a blob to a new user.

abiDocs.name: setNotTransferable
abiDocs.details: Set a blob to not be transferable.

abiDocs.name: getInfo
abiDocs.details: Get info about a blob.
abiDocs.return: flags Packed blob settings.owner Owner of the blob.revisionCount How many revisions the blob has.blockNumbers The block numbers of the revisions.

inputs.name: blobId
inputs.description: Id of the blob. This blobId can never be used again.

abiDocs.name: retract
abiDocs.details: Retract a blob.

abiDocs.name: setNotUpdatable
abiDocs.details: Set a blob as not updatable.

abiDocs.name: disown
abiDocs.details: Disown a blob.

abiDocs.name: getEnforceRevisions
abiDocs.details: Determine if a blob enforces revisions.
abiDocs.return: enforceRevisions True if the blob enforces revisions.

abiDocs.name: restart
abiDocs.details: Delete all a blob's revisions and replace it with a new blob.

abiDocs.name: getOwner
abiDocs.details: Get the owner of a blob.
